metadata.name: Mooncakes: Happy Mid Autumn Festival 2022 #3274
metadata.description:
To celebrate the Moon Festival with Mooncakes, we have created a quest to introduce everyone to fxhash. As part of that quest on mooncakes.fun, users are encouraged to mint this generative token.

This is a layered image composition using the Mooncakes site images on a 1920x1080 canvas. The image elements are randomly assigned position, scale, tint, and blur according to a ruleset which generates a Mid Autumn Festival scene made up of: Moon, Clouds, Stars, Lanterns, and Lotuses.

Special filters, shapes and colors are included as rare features, as well as a couple of surprises.

metadata.name: 10SCII #390
metadata.description:
10SCII is my take on the famous 10 PRINT program.

10 PRINT CHR$(205.5+RND(1)); : GOTO 10 is a single line program that produces a simple but visually appealing set of forward and backward slashes.

This project riffs on the original idea by removing the vertical space between lines and widening the horizontal gap. This changes the produced pieces from a maze of slashes into a series of towers. This is then rendered and animated as ASCII.

Visit https://10print.org/ to learn more about the original program that inspired this piece.

metadata.name: butterfly Effect #6
metadata.description:
The idea that something small, like getting coffee, can have much larger effects, such as altering your career is called the butterfly effect. The butterfly effect rests on the notion that the world is deeply interconnected, such that one small occurrence can influence a much larger complex system.
---------------

In this work, we have tried to make this effect schematically for you.

---------------
Eddy.
1/19/2023

metadata.name: Acrylic #147
metadata.description:
A deep dive into particles is what led me to acrylic. Bright and deep colours with smooth lines while all connected in the journey to the target. 
My main inspiration was the smooth movement of a flock to a endpoint and where a particle should go if not one but multiple points present itself. Make sure you take a look at the live view to see every detail of the piece. 


Generated with code using p5.js
Images are generated at 1280 x 2048px 
(all the way up to 7680 * 12288). 

[Options]:
To save a PNG file, please press 'S'.

[URL variables in live view]:
Change size (up to 6): /&density=6
